snippet: A cross-country trip is still fresh in the mind of an Irish immigrant in “The Compass Rose,” part of the 1st Irish Festival.
abstract: Rachel Saltz reviews Ronan Noone play The Compass Rose, directed by David Sullivan and starring Olivia Horton at Ryan's Daughter pub and theater; show is offered as part of 1st annual Irish Festival.
lead_paragraph: A cross-country trip is still fresh in the mind of an Irish immigrant in “The Compass Rose,” part of the 1st Irish Festival.
